com.opensymphony.module.sitemesh.filter

Class RoutablePrintWriter

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.io.Writer
      • java.io.PrintWriter
        • com.opensymphony.module.sitemesh.filter.RoutablePrintWriter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    SitemeshWriter, java.io.Closeable, java.io.Flushable, java.lang.Appendable, java.lang.AutoCloseable

    public class RoutablePrintWriter
extends java.io.PrintWriter
implements SitemeshWriter
    Provides a PrintWriter that routes through to another PrintWriter, however the destination can be changed at any point. The destination can be passed in using a factory, so it will not be created until it's actually needed.
    Version:
    $Revision: 1.1 $
    Author:
    Joe Walnes

      • writeSitemeshBufferFragment

        public boolean writeSitemeshBufferFragment(SitemeshBufferFragment bufferFragment)
                                    throws java.io.IOException
        Description copied from interface: SitemeshWriter
        Write a sitemesh buffer fragment to the writer. This may not be written immediately, it may be stored and written later, when this buffer is written out to a writer.
        Specified by:
        writeSitemeshBufferFragment in interface SitemeshWriter
        Parameters:
        bufferFragment - The buffer fragment to write
        Returns:
        True if the buffer was written immediately, or false if it will be written later
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - If an IOException occurred
